==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alman
<hw>Al"man</hw> <pr>(-m⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>Aleman</ets>, F. <ets>Allemand</ets>, fr.
L. <ets>Alemanni</ets>, ancient Ger. tribes.]</ety> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A German.</def> <specif>Also</specif>
<def2><pos>adj.</pos>, <def>German.</def></def2>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The German language.</def> <rj><au>J.
Foxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A kind of dance. See <er>Allemande</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Almain rivets</b></col>, <col><b>Almayne
rivets</b></col>, or <col><b>Alman rivets</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a sort
of light armor from Germany, characterized by overlapping plates,
arranged to slide on rivets, and thus afford great
flexibility.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alma Mater</ent>⟦br⟧
